As the Russia-Ukraine war entered the third week, Russian forces suffered yet another major casualty as Colonel Andrei Zakharov, who received an order of courage award by Putin in 2016, was killed on Thursday by the Ukrainian forces in a battle in Kyiv. He becomes the third top Russian military commander to be killed in this war. Eelier, Russian Major General Vitaly Gerasimov and Major General Andrei Sukhovetskiy were killed in the battle.